<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,1626,1942]" pageId="20" pageNumber="97">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,1771,1797]" pageId="20" pageNumber="97">Remarks:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Verrill" authorityYear="1899" box="[326,449,1771,1797]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Amphiuridae" genus="Amphiodia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="20" pageNumber="97" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[326,449,1771,1797]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="97">Amphiodia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName authorityName="- A. M. Clark" authorityYear="1970" box="[458,622,1771,1798]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Amphiuridae" genus="Amphiodia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="20" pageNumber="97" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="microplax" subGenus="Amphispina">
(
<emphasis box="[467,484,1772,1798]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="97">A</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[509,622,1771,1797]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="97">microplax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[679,696,1772,1798]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="97">A</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[712,845,1771,1798]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Amphiuridae" genus="Amphiodia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="20" pageNumber="97" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="obtecta" subGenus="Amphispina">
(
<emphasis box="[721,738,1772,1798]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="97">A</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[763,845,1771,1797]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="97">obtecta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are difficult to distinguish and may have been confused (
<bibRefCitation author="Mortensen, T." box="[228,417,1807,1833]" pageId="20" pageNumber="97" pagination="55 - 112" refId="ref16691" refString="Mortensen, T. (1940) Echinoderms from the Iranian Gulf. Asteroidea, Ophiuroidea, and Echinoidea. Danish Scientific Investigations in Iran, Part 2, 55 - 112." type="book chapter" year="1940">Mortensen 1940</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Stohr, S. &amp; Cinar, M. E. &amp; Dagli, E." box="[430,626,1807,1834]" pageId="20" pageNumber="97" pagination="45 - 57" refId="ref18476" refString="Stohr, S., Cinar, M. E. &amp; Dagli, E. (2010) Brittle stars (Echinodermata: Ophiuroidea) from the southern coast of Turkey (eastern Mediterranean): new records and revision of Amphiodia obtecta Mortensen, 1940. Zootaxa, 2483 (1), 45 - 57. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 2483.1.4" type="journal article" year="2010">
Stöhr 
<emphasis box="[499,550,1807,1833]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="97">et al</emphasis>
. 2010
</bibRefCitation>
). They differ in the ventral disc, which lacks scales in 
<taxonomicName box="[1250,1364,1807,1834]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Amphiuridae" genus="Amphiodia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="20" pageNumber="97" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="obtecta">
<emphasis box="[1250,1267,1808,1834]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="97">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1282,1364,1807,1833]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="97">obtecta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but is fully scaled in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="- A. M. Clark" authorityYear="1970" box="[320,464,1843,1870]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Amphiuridae" genus="Amphiodia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="20" pageNumber="97" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="microplax">
<emphasis box="[320,337,1844,1870]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="97">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[352,464,1843,1869]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="97">microplax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Both have spiny processes distal to the radial shields and marginal dorsal disc scales with spiny extensions (
<bibRefCitation author="Stohr, S. &amp; Cinar, M. E. &amp; Dagli, E." box="[409,601,1879,1905]" pageId="20" pageNumber="97" pagination="45 - 57" refId="ref18476" refString="Stohr, S., Cinar, M. E. &amp; Dagli, E. (2010) Brittle stars (Echinodermata: Ophiuroidea) from the southern coast of Turkey (eastern Mediterranean): new records and revision of Amphiodia obtecta Mortensen, 1940. Zootaxa, 2483 (1), 45 - 57. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 2483.1.4" type="journal article" year="2010">
Stöhr 
<emphasis box="[478,535,1879,1905]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="97">et al.</emphasis>
2010
</bibRefCitation>
), which places them in the subgenus 
<taxonomicName authority="Nielsen, 1932" authorityName="Nielsen" authorityYear="1932" box="[1018,1315,1879,1905]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Amphiuridae" genus="Amphiodia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="20" pageNumber="97" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Amphispina">
<emphasis box="[1018,1152,1879,1905]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="97">Amphispina</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Nielsen, E." box="[1159,1315,1879,1905]" pageId="20" pageNumber="97" pagination="241 - 346" refId="ref16969" refString="Nielsen, E. (1932) Papers from Dr. Th. Mortensen's Pacific Expedition 1914 - 16. LIX. Ophiurans from the Gulf of Panama, California, and the Strait of Georgia. Videnskabelige Meddelelser fra Dansk Naturhistorisk Forening, 91, 241 - 346." type="journal article" year="1932">Nielsen, 1932</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
as defined by A. M. 
<bibRefCitation author="Clark, A. M." box="[258,405,1915,1941]" pageId="20" pageNumber="97" pagination="1 - 81" refId="ref14094" refString="Clark, A. M. (1970) Notes on the family Amphiuridae (Ophiuroidea). Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History), 19, 1 - 81. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 24085" type="journal article" year="1970">Clark (1970)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
